-- Herrenknecht to Open Tunneling Drill Plant in Brazil, Folha Says
-- B y   F a b i o l a   M o u r a
-- 2012-03-04T14:49:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-04/herrenknecht-to-open-tunneling-drill-plant-in-brazil-folha-says.html
Germany ’s Herrenknecht AG plans to
open a tunneling machine factory in  Brazil  by 2013, Folha de Sao
Paulo newspaper  reported , citing the company’s general director
for the South American country, Juan Manuel Altstadt.  Herrenknecht expects to invest 15 million euros (34.2
million reais) in the plant, according to the Sao Paulo-based
newspaper. The company plans to export its equipment from Brazil
to the rest of Latin America and possibly to Africa and also
wants to provide machinery for the country’s expanding oil
drilling sector, Altstadt said, according to Folha.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Fabiola Moura in Sao Paulo at 
